Class Expense

java.lang.Object
Expense
public class Expense extends Object
The Expense class is used to show the financial expense transaction in the expense tracking system. It can handle both cash and digital bank transactions.

This class supports four different types of expense scenarios:

  • Digital expenses with bank details and category
  • Digital expenses with bank details but without category
  • Cash expenses without bank details but with category
  • Cash expenses without bank details and without category
Version:
0.2
Author:
Magdaluyo, Alaine Carlo R., Cruz, Zachary Andre A.

  • Constructor Details

    • Expense

      public Expense(String expenseID, String bankName, String bankAccNum, float amount, String currency, String refNum, String receiverAccNo, DateTime dateTime, String category)
      Constructs a complete Expense object with bank details and category. Used for digital expenses that requires full transaction tracking.
      Parameters:
      expenseID - the unique identifier for the expense
      bankName - the name of the bank where the transaction occurred
      bankAccNum - the account number used for the transaction
      amount - the monetary amount of the expense
      currency - the currency of the expense (e.g., "PHP")
      refNum - the transaction reference number
      receiverAccNo - the receiver's account number
      dateTime - the date and time of the expense
      category - the category classification of the expense
